value.value: A phyllome margin (PO:0025018) that is part of a bract (PO:0009055).
A leaf margin (PO:0020128) that is part of a cotyledon (PO:0020030).
A phyllome margin (PO:0025018) that is part of a prophyll (PO:0009042).
A phyllome margin (PO:0025018) that is part of scale leaf (PO:0006003).
A phyllome margin (PO:0025018) that is part of a tepal (PO:0009033).
A phyllome margin (PO:0025018) that is part of a sporophyll (PO:0009026).
A whole plant (PO:0000003) that arises through meiosis and is contained in a spore wall.

definition.value: A spore is usually single-celled in homosporous plants but may be multicellular in heterosporous plants. May have a spore wall (GO:0031160) made of sporopollenin.

value.value: A plant organ margin (PO:0025005) that is part of a phyllome lamina (PO:0025396).
The margin of a carpel.

definition.value: Only flattened carpels can have a margin.

value.value: The margin of a stamen.

definition.value: Only flattened stamens can have a margin.

value.value: A perianth (PO:0009058) consisting of one or more tepals (PO:0009033).

definition.value: This structure is a perianth (PO:0009058) where there is no differentiation between calyx (PO:0009060) and corolla (PO:0009059).

value.value: A collective phyllome structure (PO:0025023) composed of two or more leaves (PO:0025034).

definition.value: This term replaces the obsolete term leaf whorl (PO:0008034). If you are looking for annotations for PO:0008034, please use this term instead.

value.value: A collective plant organ structure (PO:0025007) that consists of two or more phyllomes (PO:0006001) originating from the same node or from one or more adjacent nodes with compressed shoot internodes (PO:0005005).
A shoot axis node (PO:0005004) that is part of a branch (PO:0025073).
A collective plant organ structure (PO:0025007) that produces root meristems (PO:0006085), the plant structures (PO:0009011) that arise from them and the parts thereof.

definition.value: Generally the below ground portion of a vascular plant.

value.value: A native plant cell (PO:0025606) that is part of an embryo sac (PO:0025074).
A native plant cell (PO:0025606) that is part of a plant embryo (PO:0009009).
A plant axis (PO:0025004) that is part of a shoot system (PO:0009006).

definition.value: Often bears leaves and branches. In vascular plants, has at least one node and one internode.

value.value: A native plant cell (PO:0025606) that is part of a portion of ground tissue (PO:0025059).

definition.value: Includes parenchyma, collenchyma and sclerenchyma cells.

value.value: A ground tissue cell (PO:0025030) that contains latex.

definition.value: May be simple or branched.

value.value: A native plant cell (PO:0025606) that is dead at maturity, lacks specialized wall thickenings or lignin, and has tapered ends that are thin and partially hydrolyzed.

definition.value: Hydroids are water and mineral conducting cells found in bryophytes in axes and leaves in the gametophytic phase and in the seta in the sporophytic phase.

value.value: A native plant cell (PO:0025606) that resembles in structure the sieve elements (PO:0025406) of vascular plants.

definition.value: A carbohydrate and amino acid conducting cell found in bryophytes in axes and leaves in the gametophyte development stage (PO:0028003) and in the seta in the sporophytic phase. Leptoids have no nucleus at maturity. Carbohydrate and amino acid conducting cells in bryophytes range from conducting parenchyma cells that are indistinguishable from other parenchyma cells to 'leptoids sensu strictu' that are structurally comparable to sieve elements in vascular plants, as well as many intermediate forms. The term leptoid is used for cells that are distinguishable from other parenchyma cells, whether they be intermediate or leptoids sensu strictu.

value.value: A phyllome (PO:0006001) that is not associated with a reproductive structure.
A portion of parenchyma (PO:0005421) specialized for carbohydrate storage.

definition.value: This tissue could be found in any organ, but often occurs in fruits or tubers. New GO term carbohydrate storage has been requested.

value.value: A portion of storage parenchyma (PO:0025035) that is part of a tuber (PO:0025522).

definition.value: This is the flesh of a tuber. See part_of children for individual components of tuber flesh. If you are annotating to this term, please add an additional annotation to either shoot axis tuber (PO:0004543) or tuberous root tuber (PO:0025476).

value.value: A portion of storage parenchyma that is part of a fruit.

definition.value: If you are annotating to this term, please add an additional annotation to the specific type of fruit (PO:0009001), such as achene fruit (PO:0030107), berry fruit (PO:0030108), capsule fruit (PO:0030091), caryopsis fruit (PO:0030104), drupe fruit (PO:0030103), follicle fruit (PO:0030105), legume fruit (PO:0030100), nut fruit (PO:0030102), samara fruit (PO:0030099), schizocarp fruit (PO:0030098), silique fruit (PO:0030106), or their subclasses, depending on the species.

value.value: A portion of tuber storage parenchyma (PO:0025035) that is part of a subterranean tuber (PO:0004547).

definition.value: This term is used to refer to potato tuber flesh. See part_of children for individual components of subterranean tuber flesh.

value.value: A portion of tuber storage parenchyma (PO:0025036) that is part of an aerial tuber (PO:0004548).

definition.value: See part_of children for individual components of aerial tuber flesh.

label.value: shoot axis tuber axillary vegetative bud

value.value: An axillary vegetative bud (PO:0004712) that is part of a shoot axis tuber (PO:0004543).
A tuber axillary vegetative bud that is part of an aerial tuber.
A tuber axillary vegetative bud that is part of a subterranean tuber.

definition.value: A structure on the tuber surface that can sprout. In potatoes, axillary vegetative buds (eyes) can determine processing quality. Scale that the breeders use to rate the buds/sprouts of tubers: 1. none, 2. swollen eye, 3. sprout ca. 1/4 inch, 4. sprout ca. 1/2 inch, 5. sprout ca. 1 inch, 6. sprout ca. 2 inch, 7. sprout ca. 3 inch, 8. new top growth, 9. chain tubers.

value.value: A portion of shoot axis periderm (PO:0005048) that is part of a shoot axis tuber (PO:0004543).
A portion of tuber periderm that is part of an aerial tuber.
A portion of tuber periderm that is part of a subterranean tuber.

definition.value: The skin of young potatoes is epidermis while the skin of mature potatoes is periderm.

value.value: A portion of shoot axis epidermis (PO:0000112) that is part of a shoot axis tuber (PO:0004543).
A portion of shoot axis tuber epidermis (PO:0025046) that is part of an aerial tuber (PO:0004548).
A shoot axis tuber epidermis (PO:0025046) that is part of a subterranean shoot axis tuber (PO:0004547).

definition.value: The skin of young potatoes is epidermis while the skin of mature potatoes is periderm.

value.value: A tuber interfascicular region that is part of a subterranean tuber storage parenchyma.

definition.value: Because subterranean interfascicular regions in potato tubers form before the subterranean tuber perimedullary zone expands (PO:0025063), in mature potato tubers, the subterranean tuber interfascicular regions persist as rays that extend from the central pith to the eyes or subterranean tuber axillary vegetative buds (PO:0025042).

value.value: An interfascicular region that is part of a tuber storage parenchyma.
A tuber interfascicular region that is part of an aerial tuber storage parenchyma.
A portion of pith (PO:0006109) that is part of a tuber storage parenchyma (PO:0025036).
A portion of tuber pith (PO:0025052) that is part of a subterranean tuber storage parenchyma (PO:0025038).

definition.value: In potatoes, this is part of the flesh.

value.value: A portion of tuber pith (PO:0025052) that is part of an aerial tuber storage parenchyma (PO:0025039).
A portion of cortex (PO:0005708) that is part of a tuber storage parenchyma (PO:0025036).
A portion of tuber cortex that is part of an aerial tuber storage parenchyma.
A portion of tuber cortex that is part of a subterranean tuber storage parenchyma.
A portion of parenchyma (PO:0005421) that is the outer layer of the pith (PO:0006109).

definition.value: The term perimedullary zone is only used when the outer layer of the pith is distinct from the inner layer.

value.value: Any portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) other than epidermis (PO:0005679) or vascular tissue (PO:0009015).

definition.value: Develops from the ground meristem (PO:0025594).

value.value: A cardinal part of multi-tissue plant structure (PO:0025498) that is thin and flat.

definition.value: PATO:0000407 (flat) and PATO:0000592 (thin).

value.value: A perimedullary zone (PO:0025058) that is part of a tuber pith (PO:0025052).
